    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0dd8cb6b_b56692d1",
        "filename": "android/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/ColorBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 277,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-06T03:01:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done; I left Vulkan out because even on Android apparently[1], Vulkan\u0027s swap chain and window system interface avoids the use of EGL (and thus a lot of libOpenglRender).\n\nAlso, Vulkan\u0027s multithreaded command submission doesn\u0027t fit with the current RenderThread/RenderContext organization, and there are probably different (or better) ways to blit colorbuffers / post them to the screen, so we\u0027d be looking at a pretty hardcore rewrite of libOpenGLRender.\n\n[1] https://github.com/googlesamples/android-vulkan-tutorials/blob/master/tutorial04_first_window/app/src/main/jni/VulkanMain.cpp",
      "parentUuid": "0d6b6b00_481382d4",
